(
<figureCitation box="[159,273,752,779]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1756,1780]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox-0="[169,1419,802,1723]" captionTargetBox-1="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId-0="figure-80@2.[151,1435,800,1730]" captionTargetId-1="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–4. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. ♂ 1. Dorsal habitus; 2. Lateral habitus; 3. Head and thorax; 4. Face. Scale bars: 1–4 = 1.0 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911357" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6911357/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Figs 1–12</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911357" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6911357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911357/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" startId="2.[151,264,1756,1780]" targetBox="[169,1419,802,1723]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1756,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,672,1756,1781]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
FIGURES 1–4. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yao &amp; Dietrich &amp; Xing, 2022" authorityName="Yao &amp; Dietrich &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,584,1756,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tambocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fanjingensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[322,584,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Tambocerus fanjingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[591,672,1757,1781]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
♂ 1. Dorsal habitus; 2. Lateral habitus; 3. Head and thorax; 4. Face. Scale bars: 1–4 = 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1862,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1862,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Description.</emphasis>
Color pattern typical for genus.Vertex with median length 0.35x basal width between eyes. Head in dorsal view slightly narrower than pronotum. Fore femur with one dorsoapical seta, row AM with 2 stout setae, and row IC with 3 stout setae and several short setae. Hind femur setal formula 2+2+1. Hind tibia row PD with 21 macrosetae; row AD with approximately 13 long stout setae and 0–4 short and stout setae between each long seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1862,2033]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,150,645]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis box="[151,325,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer elongate, triangularly produced into straight spinelike process posteriorly, with scattered fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[271,370,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation box="[584,651,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate abruptly narrowing at midlength, apical half slender with three stout macrosetae and several short setae (
<figureCitation box="[746,816,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft in ventral view broad, 1/3 as wide as long in ventral view, lateral margins with serrations (
<figureCitation box="[749,818,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); aedeagus in lateral view strongly curved dorsally, Cshaped, apex expanded with a small triangular lamellar process in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1139,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); gonopore apical (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
). Connective stem twice as long as arms (
<figureCitation box="[647,728,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Style broad at base, abruptly narrowing subapically, preapical lobe with setae (
<figureCitation box="[334,418,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[166,1416,670,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-209@3.[156,1431,669,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–12. Tambocerus fanjingensis sp. nov. 5. Pygofer, lateral view; 6. Pygofer, dorsal view; 7. Valve, ventral view; 8. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, ventral view; 12. Style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–12 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
