<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Qu &amp; Dai, 2014" authorityName="Qu &amp; Dai" authorityYear="2014" box="[665,1041,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tambocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustispinus">
<emphasis box="[665,844,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">T. robustispinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Qu, L. &amp; Dai, R. H." box="[853,1041,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" pagination="47 - 55" refId="ref2930" refString="Qu, L. &amp; Dai, R. H. (2014) Three new species of the leafhopper genus Tambocerus Zhang &amp; Webb (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) from southern China. ZooKeys, 434, 47 - 55." type="journal article" year="2014">Qu &amp; Dai, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the later by the relatively broad, parallel-sided aedeagal shaft in posterior view with the lateral margins serrate throughout their length and the apex lacking distinct processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1002,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,645]" box="[199,1002,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species is named after its 
<typeStatus box="[738,786,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="90">type</typeStatus>
locality “Fanjing”.
</paragraph>
